Leipzig: Breitkopf, 1742&ndash;44.</li>

<li>Burckhardt, Jakob, <em>Die Kultur der Renaissance in Italien</em>,
Basel: Schweighauser, 1860. English translation: <em>The Civilization
of the Renaissance in Italy</em>, tr. S. G. C. Middlemore, introd.
Peter Burke, notes Peter Murray, London: Penguin Books, 1990.</li>

<li>Copernicus, Nicolaus, <em>De revolutionibus orbium coelestium
libri VI</em>, Nuremberg: Johannes Petrejus, 1543. Bruno read either
this first edition or the second, 1566, edition published by Heinrich
Petri at Nuremberg. English translation: <em>On the Revolutions</em>,
tr. and commentary Edward Rosen, London: Macmillan, 1978.</li>

<li>Dionysius the Areopagite, pseudo-, <em>The Divine Names.</em>
Composed in the late fifth or early sixth century AD. Translated in
