 with the English translation by Mulligan, MacGlynn and Schmidt, under
the
 title<em><a href="https://aquinas.cc/la/en/~QDeVer" target="other"> Disputed Questions about Truth</a>.</em></li>
 
<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, <em>Scriptum super libros Sententiarum
magistri Petri Lombardi</em> (incomplete: up to <em>Super IV
Sent.</em>, dist. 22 only), 4 vols, eds Pierre Mandonnet and M. Fabien
Moos, Paris: P. Lethielleux, 1929&ndash;56. Composed 1252&ndash;1256.
The Latin text of the complete work, together with an English
translation by Chris Decaen, Beth Mortensen and Dylan Schrader,
is
 <a href="https://aquinas.cc/la/en/~Sent.IV">available online (Aquinas Institute)</a>.</li>
 
<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, <em>Summa theologiae</em>, with the
commentary of Tommaso de Vio (Cardinal Cajetan), in Thomas Aquinas,
<em>Opera omnia</em>, as above, vols 4&ndash;12. The <em>Summa</em>
was composed between 1267 and 1273, but remained unfinished at
Thomas&rsquo;s death in 1274. The Latin text with an English
translation by Lawrence Shapcote is
 <a href="https://aquinas.cc/la/en/~ST.I">available online (Aquinas Institute)</a>.</li>
 
<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, <em>Super primum[&ndash;secundam] epistolam
ad Corinthios lectura</em>, in: Thomas Aquinas, <em>Super Epistolas S.
Pauli lectura</em>, ed. Raffaele Cai, 8th revised ed., Turin:
Marietti, 1953. The Latin text with an English translation by Fabian
R. Larcher and Matthew Lamb is
 <a href="https://aquinas.cc/la/en/~1Cor" target="other">available online (Aquinas Institute)</a>.</li>
 
<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, <em>Super librum De causis expositio</em>,
ed. H. D. Saffrey, Fribourg and Louvain, Soci&eacute;t&eacute;
philosophique, 1954. The Latin text with an English translation (of
unspecified authorship) is
 <a href="https://aquinas.cc/la/en/~LibCaus" target="other">available online (Aquinas Institute)</a>.
 Composed c. 1272.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, <em>Expositio Libri Physicorum</em>, in:
Thomas Aquinas <em>Opera omnia</em> (as above), vol. 2. Composed
1268&ndash;1270. English translation: <em>Commentary on
Aristotle&rsquo;s Physics</em>, tr. Richard J. Blackwell, Richard J.
Spath, W. Edmund Thirlkel and Pierre H. Conway, New Haven: Yale
University Press, 1963; reprinted: Notre Dame, IN: Dumb Ox Books,
1999. The Latin text with this English translation is
 <a href="https://aquinas.cc/la/en/~Phys" target="other">available online (Aquinas Institute)</a>.</li>
 
<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, <em>De principiis naturae</em> (<em>On the
Principles of Nature</em>), in Thomas Aquinas, <em>Opera omnia</em>,
vol. 43. Composed c. 1255. English translation: Joseph Bobik,
<em>Aquinas on Matter and Form and the Elements. A Translation and
Interpretation of the <span class="plain">De principiis naturae</span>
and the <span class="plain">De mixtione elementorum</span> of St.
Thomas Aquinas</em>, Notre Dame, IN: University of Notre Dame Press,
1998. The Latin text with an English translation by Roman A. Kocourek
is
 <a href="https://aquinas.cc/la/en/~DePrinNat" target="other">available online (Aquinas Institute)</a>.</li>
 
<li>Veyssi&egrave;re de Lacroze, Mathurin, <em>Entretiens sur divers
sujets d&rsquo;histoire, de litt&eacute;rature, de religion et de
critique</em>, Cologne: Pierre Marteau, 1711.</li>

<li>Virgil, [Works, including the <em>Aeneid</em>], Latin texts ed.,
with English tr., by H. Ruston Fairclough, 2 vols, Cambridge, MA:
Harvard University Press (Loeb Classical Library), 1918&ndash;26.
Virgil died in 19 BC, before completing his revision of the
<em>Aeneid</em>.</li>
</ul>

<h3 id="SecoSour">Secondary Literature</h3>

<h4 id="StudCiteEntrSeleStud">Studies cited in this entry and selected studies</h4>

<ul class="hanging">

<li>Aquilecchia, Giovanni, 1995, &ldquo;Giordano Bruno in Inghilterra
(1583&ndash;1585). Documenti e testimonianze&rdquo;, <em>Bruniana
&amp; Campanelliana</em>, 1: 21&ndash;42.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2001, <em>Giordano Bruno</em>, Turin:
Aragno. (A revised version of the 1971 edition, also published as an
entry to the <em>Dizionario biografico degli italiani</em>, vol. 14
 (1972),  <a href="http://www.treccani.it/enciclopedia/giordano-bruno_(Dizionario-Biografico)/" target="other">available on line</a>.
 Based on a careful reading of the available documentation and free of
the supposition that colours many biographies.)</li>

<li>Blum, Paul Richard, 2012, <em>Giordano Bruno. An
Introduction</em>, tr. Peter Henneveld, Amsterdam: Rodopi.
(Recommended for those unfamiliar with Bruno&rsquo;s life and
works.)</li>

<li>Brown, Stuart, 2002, &ldquo;Monadology and the Reception of Bruno
in the Young Leibniz&rdquo;, in Gatti 2002, 381&ndash;403.</li>

<li>Canone, Eugenio, and others, 2000, <em>Giordano Bruno
1548&ndash;1600. Mostra storico documentaria, Roma, Biblioteca
Casanatense, 7 giugno&ndash;30 settembre 2000</em>, Florence: Olschki.
(A visual tour of Bruno&rsquo;s life and works.)</li>

<li>Del Prete, Antonella. 2023. &ldquo;&Agrave; la crois&eacute;e de
traditions diff&eacute;rentes. Giordano Bruno et la doctrine des
&eacute;l&eacute;ments&rdquo;, in <em>De mundi recentioribus
ph&aelig;nomenis. Cosmologie et science dans l&rsquo;Europe des Temps
modernes. XVe-XVIIe si&egrave;cles. Essais en l&rsquo;honneur de
Miguel &Aacute;ngel Granada</em>, eds &Eacute;douard Mehl and
Isabelle Pantin, Turnhout: Brepols, 2023, 183&ndash;205.</li>

<li>Gatti, Hilary (ed.), 2002, <em>Giordano Bruno. Philosopher of the
Renaissance</em>, Ashgate: Aldershot.</li>

<li>Gatti, Hilary, 2011, <em>Essays on Giordano Bruno</em>, Princeton:
Princeton University Press.</li>

<li>Granada, Miguel &Aacute;ngel, 1990, &ldquo;L&rsquo;interpretazione
bruniana di Copernico e la <em>Narratio prima</em> di Rheticus&rdquo;,
<em>Rinascimento</em>, 30: 343&ndash;365.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash; 1994, &ldquo;Il rifiuto della distinzione
fra <em>potentia absoluta</em> e <em>potentia ordinata</em> di Dio e
l&rsquo;affermazione dell&rsquo;universo infinito in Giordano
Bruno&rdquo;, <em>Rivista di storia della filosofia</em>, new series,
49: 495&ndash;532.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2000, &ldquo;&lsquo;Voi siete dissolubili,
ma non vi dissolverete&rsquo;. Il problema della dissoluzione dei
mondi in Giordano Bruno&rdquo;, <em>Paradigmi</em>, 18:
261&ndash;289.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2005, <em>La reivindicaci&oacute;n de la
filosof&iacute;a en Giordano Bruno</em>. Barcelona: Herder.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2008, &ldquo;Kepler and Bruno on the
Infinity of the Universe and of Solar Systems&rdquo;, <em>Journal of
the History of Astronomy</em>, 39: 469&ndash;495.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2020, &ldquo;Libro I. La relazione
Dio/mondo e la necessit&agrave; dell&rsquo;universo infinito&rdquo;,
in Granada and Tessicini, 2020, 47&ndash;69.</li>

<li>Granada, Miguel &Aacute;ngel, and Tessicini, Dario (eds), 2020,
<em>Giordano Bruno, </em>De immenso,<em>  Letture
critiche</em>, Pisa: Fabrizio Serra.</li>

<li>Knox, Dilwyn, 2001, &ldquo;Bruno&rsquo;s Doctrine of Gravity,
Levity and Natural Circular Motion&rdquo;, <em>Physis</em>, new
series, 38:171&ndash;209. (Published 2002.)</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2013. &ldquo;Bruno: Immanence and
Transcendence in <em>De la causa, principio et uno</em>, Dialogue
II&rdquo;, <em>Bruniana &amp; Campanelliana</em>, 19:
463&ndash;482.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2020a, &ldquo;<em>De immenso</em> II.
La perfezione dell&rsquo;universo&rdquo;, in Granada and Tessicini,
2020, 71&ndash;102.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2020b, &ldquo;Wonder and the
Philosopher&rsquo;s Perfection: Giordano Bruno&rdquo;, in Francesca
Bugliani Knox and Jennifer Reek (eds), <em>Poetry, Philosophy and
Theology in Conversation. Thresholds of Wonder</em>, London,
Routledge. Pp. 29&ndash;49.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2021, &ldquo;The World Soul and
Individual Souls. Two Notes on Giordano Bruno&rsquo;s <em>Lampas
triginta statuarum</em>&rdquo;, in: <em>Giordano
Bruno.  Law, Philosophy, and Theology in the Early Modern
Era</em>, ed. Massimiliano Traversino Di Cristo, Paris, Garnier.
Pp. 275&ndash;300.</li>

<li>Lai, Tyrone, 1973, &ldquo;Nicholas of Cusa and the Finite
Universe&rdquo;, <em>Journal of the History of Philosophy</em>,
11:161&ndash;167.</li>

<li>McFarland, Thomas, 1969, <em>Coleridge and the Pantheist
Tradition</em>, Oxford: Clarendon.</li>

<li>Michel, Paul-Henri, 1962, <em>La Cosmologie de Giordano
Bruno</em>, Paris: Hermann. Translated as <em>The Cosmology of
Giordano Bruno</em>, tr. R. E. W. Maddison, Paris: Hermann, 1973.</li>

<li>Nelson, John Charles, 1958, <em>Renaissance Theory of Love. The
Context of Giordano Bruno&rsquo;s</em> Eroici furori. New York:
Columbia University Press.</li>

<li>Ricci, Saverio, 1990, <em>La fortuna del pensiero di Giordano
Bruno, 1600&ndash;1750</em>, Florence: Le Lettere.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2000, <em>Giordano Bruno nell&rsquo;Europa
del Cinquecento</em>, Rome: Salerno.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2009, <em>Dal</em> Brunus redivivus <em>al
Bruno degli italiani. Metamorfosi della nolana filosofia tra sette e
ottocento</em>, Rome: Edizioni di storia e letteratura.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2104, &ldquo;Le proc&egrave;s de Giordano
Bruno par l&rsquo;Inquisition&rdquo;, <em>Lexicon philosophicum</em>,
2: 97&ndash;125.
 [<a href="http://lexicon.cnr.it/index.php/LP/article/view/400/324" target="other">Ricci 2014 available online</a>]</li>
 
<li>Rowland, Ingrid D., 2008, <em>Giordano Bruno. Philosopher,
Heretic</em>, New York: Farrar, Straus and Giroux. (Recommended
for those unfamiliar with Bruno&rsquo;s life and works.)</li>

<li>Segonds, Alain&ndash;Philippe, 2000, &ldquo;Notes&rdquo;; see
Firpo 2000.</li>

<li>Spruit, Leen, 1988, <em>Il problema della conoscenza in Giordano
Bruno</em>, Naples: Bibliopolis.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1989, &ldquo;Motivi peripatetici nella
gnoseologia bruniana dei dialoghi italiani&rdquo;, <em>Verifiche</em>,
18: 367&ndash;399.</li>

<li>Sturlese, Rita, 1987. &ldquo;&lsquo;Et Nolanus vivat, recipiatur,
adoretur&rsquo;. Le note del &lsquo;Postillatore napoletano&rsquo; al
dialogo <em>De l&rsquo;infinito</em> di Giordano Bruno&rdquo;, in
<em>Scritti in onore di Eugenio Garin</em>, Pisa: Scuola Normale
Superiore, Pisa. Pp. 117&ndash;128.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1994, &ldquo;Le fonti del <em>Sigillus
sigillorum</em> del Bruno, ossia: il confronto con Ficino a Oxford
sull&rsquo;anima umana&rdquo;, <em>Nouvelles de la R&eacute;publique
des Lettres</em>, anno 1994, 89&ndash;167.</li>

<li>Tessicini, Dario, 2007, <em>I dintorni dell&rsquo;infinito.
Giordano Bruno e l&rsquo;astronomia del Cinquecento</em>, Pisa:
Fabrizio Serra. (Valuable for an understanding of what Bruno did
and did not understand about astronomy.)</li>

<li>Yates, Frances A., 1964, <em>Giordano Bruno and the Hermetic
Tradition</em>, London: Routledge adn Kegan Paul. (Readable,
informative, even if the overall interpretation is no longer
considered sound.)</li>
</ul>

<h4 id="Bibl">Bibliographies (ordered chronologically)</h4>

<ul class="hanging">

<li>Salvestrini, Virgilio, 1958, <em>Bibliografia di Giordano Bruno
(1582&ndash;1950)</em>, second revised edition by Luigi Firpo,
Florence: Sansoni.</li>

<li>Severini, Maria Elena, 2002, <em>Bibliografia di Giordano Bruno,
1951&ndash;2000</em>, Sussidi eruditi, 58, Rome: Edizioni di storia e
letteratura.</li>

<li>Figorilli, Maria Cristina, 2003, <em>Per una bibliografia di
Giordano Bruno, 1800&ndash;1999</em>, Paris: Les Belles lettres.</li>

<li>Gatti, Hilary, &lsquo;Giordano Bruno&rsquo;, first instantiation
2104, regularly updated thereafter, in the <em>Oxford
Bibliographies</em> online resource; accessible by subscription
only.</li>
</ul>

<h4 id="AddiReso">Additional Resources</h4>

<ul class="hanging">

<li>Canone, Eugenio, and Ernst, Germana (eds), 1995&ndash;,
<em>Bruniana &amp; Campanelliana</em>, Pisa, 1&ndash;. (A journal
dedicated mainly to Bruno and Campanella.)</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash; (eds), 2006&ndash;, <em>Enciclopedia
bruniana e campanelliana</em>, 1&ndash;, Pisa: Istituti
editoriali e poligrafici internazionali. (Scholarly entries on
concepts and persons mentioned by Bruno and Tommaso Campanella.)</li>

<li>Ciliberto, Michele (ed.), 2014, <em>Giordano Bruno. Parole,
concetti, immagini</em>, 3 vols, Pisa: Edizioni della Normale.
(Contains entries, with bibliographies, on most aspects of
Bruno&rsquo;s philosophy especially helpful for authors relating to
its reception.)</li>
</ul>
</div> 

