<div id="other-internet-resources">

<h2 id="Oth">Other Internet Resources</h2>

<ul>

 <li><a href="http://www.iliesi.cnr.it/AGB/index_bruno.php" target="other"><em>Archivio Giordano Bruno</em></a>,
 in the
 <a href="http://www.iliesi.cnr.it/afr/index.shtml" target="other"><em>Archivio dei filosofi italiani del Rinascimento</em></a>,
 principal editor Eugenio Canone, hosted by the Istituto per il
Lessico Intellettuale Europeo e Storia delle Idee.</li>

 <li><em><a href="http://bibliotecaideale.filosofia.sns.it/index.php" target="other">La biblioteca ideale di Giordano Bruno. Le opere e le fonti</a>,</em>
 hosted by the Istituto Nazionale di Studi sul Rinascimento,
Florence. Searchable versions of Bruno&rsquo;s Latin and Italian
works, with a list of sources used in them.</li>

 <li><a href="http://bivio.filosofia.sns.it/bvAuthorWorksList.php?authorName=Bruno%2C+Giordano&amp;authorSign=BrunoGiordano&amp;file=AuthorListGroup2.xml&amp;onlyWorksWithFigure=0" target="other">BIVIO: Biblioteca Virtuale On-Line</a>, hosted
 by the Istituto Nazionale di Studi sul Rinascimento, Florence.
Searchable versions of Italian and Latin works by Renaissance
authors.</li>

 <li><em><a href="https://warburg.sas.ac.uk/research/completed-research-projects/giordano-bruno/download-page" target="other">Bibliotheca bruniana electronica. The Complete Works of Giordano Bruno</a></em>,
 hosted by the Warburg Institute, London. The site has downloadable
PDF files of editions of Bruno&rsquo;s works and scholarly studies in
various languages.</li>

 <li><a href="https://mlat.uzh.ch/"><em>Corpus corporum repositorium operum latinorum apud universitatem Turicensem</em></a>,
 hosted by the University of Zurich under the direction of Philipp
Roelli. A searchable (meta&ndash;)repository of Latin texts
written from antiquity onwards. </li>

 <li><a href="https://eebo.chadwyck.com/home" target="other"><em>Early English Books Online</em> (EEBO).</a>
 Digital reproductions of the 1583&ndash;85 editions of Bruno&rsquo;s
Italian dialogues and his <em>Ars reminiscendi</em>.</li>
</ul>
</div>

