<div id="acknowledgments">

<h3>Acknowledgments</h3>

<p>
My thanks to: Leen Spruit and Richard Blum for their comments on, and
corrections to, the pre-publication version of this entry; Dario
Tessicini for his advice about Bruno&rsquo;s cometary theory; Hilary
Gatti for her comments on Bruno&rsquo;s insistence on the importance
of the senses and observation; Ovanes Okopyan for the section on
Soviet interpretations of Bruno; Valentina Zaffino for her various
suggestions; the anonymous SEP reviewer for supplying the reference to
the &ldquo;dark&rdquo; Heraclitus; and Ada Bronowski for her
suggestion that Lucretius&rsquo;s <em>simulacra</em> inspired, at
least in part, Bruno&rsquo;s theory that cosmic bodies emitted and
absorbed stray particles.</p>
</div> 

